MINNA  – Niger State government has intercepted a herd of 500 cattle at Kuchi and Galadima-kogo at Alawa and Erena communities in Shiroro and Munya Local Government Areas of the state, even as it promised to take care of families of security person­nel who paid the supreme prize in the fight against banditry. Commissioner of Local Government, Chieftaincy Af­fairs and Internal Security, Mr. Umar Emmanuel, disclosed this while speaking to jour­nalists on the current security situation and what the Gover­nor Abubarkar Sani Bello led administration was doing to end the siege by armed bandits, Boko-Haram and ISWAP mem­bers on some parts of the state. Interception of the 300 cows and 100 sheep by the Joint Taskforce set up by the state government, according to the commissioner, was sequel to in­telligence reports that resulted to the neutralizing of many armed bandits terrorizing ru­ral communities in the state. 2023: I’ll Rather Return Home Than Join APC – Senator… NURTW Clashes: Bode George Blames Sanwo-Olu, Says Lagos Island… Umar said some security operatives he did not give their exact number lost their lives in Shiroro and Munya, add­ing that the state government would take care of their depen­dents for sacrifices made towards protecting terri­torial integrity of Nigeria.